The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, May 14: Booming industrial activity has helped the government collect Rs 13,862 crore from excise and customs duties during the first month of the current fiscal, up 19.1 per cent from the year-ago period. The government fetched Rs 6,640 crore as excise duty against Rs 5,967 crore in the same month last . Customs duty collection jumped 27.4 per cent to Rs 7,221 crore from Rs 5,667 crore in April 2006. The government has fixed an indirect tax collection target of about Rs 2,54,528 crore for 2007-08. 

 Calcutta, May 14: Shoeb Ahmed has been appointed as SAILs director (commercial). Ahmed was previously executive director (marketing -long products) at sails headquarters in the city. He has also headed the companys corporate affairs division during 1997-2003, the statement added.

 New Delhi, May 14: Danish beer company Carlsberg has acquired a brewery in Himachal Pradesh. The company, however, did not disclose any financial details of the deal. The acquisition is carried out by the companys joint venture South Asia Breweries, in which it holds 45 per cent stake.

 New Delhi, May 14: Tech Mahindra has announced a strategic alliance with Sun Microsystems India to roll out internet protocol tv (iptv) services .




